<dl id="n54148b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54148b">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54148b"> 148(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> jussive <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54148b"><li>FW 262.f1 </li><li><a href="../../flex/ln/lexln.htm#n54148b">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/ln/l39ln.htm#n54148b">1939</a> <a href="../../flex/la/lexla.htm#f008">&nbsp;fn008</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54148b">MS BL 47478-330</ms> </li><li>JJA 53:309 <a name="lad13" href="../../FF/fdra/lda.htm#lad13">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/la/lad13.htm#n54148b">Draft: II.2&sect;1.13</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Cette mimique est, si l&apos;on peut dire, un indicatif en acte. Il tient la place d&apos;un optatif-<mark>jussif</mark>, qui oblige le fait qu&apos;il &eacute;nonce &agrave; se r&eacute;aliser. Bref, cette mimique est une formule en action. <br>[This mimicry is, so to speak, an indicative in action. It takes the place of an opt-jussive, which forces the fact that it states to come true. In short, this expression is a formula in action. <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 286</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Jussive: expressing command. In text, with Joseph Smith (who founded Mormonism). </mm> </dd></dl>
